olive oil
3 clove garlic
1 tbs honey
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tbs water
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet ginger paste
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 stalk celery
2 radish
½ fresh chilli
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 bag Asian Slaw Mix

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a small bowl, combine the honey, soy sauce, water and half the garlic. Set aside.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the sauces!

• In a large bowl, combine beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, ginger paste, the egg, chicken-style stock powder and remaining garlic.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef meatballs, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes.
• In the last minute of cook time, add honey-soy mixture and cook, stirring, until the meatballs are coated in the sauce. Remove from the heat.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery, radish and fresh chilli (if using).
• In a medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, ponzu sauce, celery, Asian slaw mix, radish and crushed peanuts. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

• Divide ponzu celery slaw between bowls. Top with honey, soy and ginger beef meatballs.
• Spoon over any remaining glaze from the pan.
• Garnish with chilli to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Chilli is spicy, leave it out if you're not a fan!